\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When the inverse relation of 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 is a function, it is denoted  
\begin_inset Formula $T^{-1}:\text{range}(T)\to A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{-1}$
\end_inset

 is called the 
\series bold
inverse function
\series default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 or simply 
\series bold
the inverse
\series default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

.
